column11: U S West, Fluor In Cellular Radio DENVER, Jan. 10 (Reuters) - U S West, one of the seven regional companies created by the breakup of the American Telephone and Telegraph Company, said it and Fluor Engineers Inc., a unit of the Fluor Corporation, had signed a letter of intent to develop a cellular radio telecommunications system. The system would serve the offshore communications needs in the Gulf from south of New Orleans to south of Corpus Christi, Tex., extending about 150 miles out to sea.
